DA  - 1989/05/01/
SN  - 0022-1996
DO  - https://doi.org/10.1016/0022-1996(89)90010-X
UR  - https://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/pii/002219968990010X
AB  - The transfer problem is studied in an overlapping generations model with government debt. The transfer is from a creditor country to a debtor country. It is shown that (a) the effects of transfers depend on their method of finance and on their method of disbursement; (b) the short-run effects of the transfers may differ from the long-run effects; and (c) the transfers may improve welfare in both countries or they may increase welfare in the country making the transfer and reduce welfare in the country receiving the transfer and these possibilities cannot be ruled out by the stability argument.
