UR  - https://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/pii/0022199689900081
AB  - Current account issues are examined in a context in which expenditure and borrowing are chosen optimally. Permanent falls in income are first discussed, and the analysis deals with fixed and endogenous discount rates and interest rates. A ‘smoothing response’ in consumption, producing a current account deficit, is shown to follow a short-term income fall. However, a long-term fall can call forth an ‘adjustment response’ with consumption and debt first moving toward the equilibrium which would obtain if the income fall were permanent.
